WEBVTT

00:02.077 --> 00:05.337
<i> - [speaking Spanish]</i>

00:08.584 --> 00:13.012
Let me help Ruby find her way
back to herself please,

00:13.163 --> 00:15.405
so we don't lose her forever.

00:15.424 --> 00:18.408
<i> [soft music]</i>

00:18.427 --> 00:22.763
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:22.915 --> 00:25.766
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

00:25.918 --> 00:32.698
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:38.097 --> 00:40.855
Smiles, everyone.

00:40.933 --> 00:43.375
Welcome.
I'm your host, Elena Roarke.

00:43.527 --> 00:47.287
- I'm Sue Beck,
the first Mrs. Gavin Beck.

00:47.439 --> 00:50.440
- Jenna Glazer-Beck,
the second Mrs. Gavin Beck.

00:50.442 --> 00:52.125
- It's so nice
to see that two ladies

00:52.278 --> 00:53.260
who were married
to the same man

00:53.295 --> 00:54.795
can get along and be friends.

00:54.871 --> 00:57.038
- Well, friends
might be pushing it.

00:57.058 --> 00:59.283
- We share a common goal.

00:59.301 --> 01:01.376
Speaking of,
when do we get started?

01:01.453 --> 01:02.561
- Oh, soon.

01:02.638 --> 01:04.521
Go ahead to my office,
and I'll be right there.

01:10.129 --> 01:11.904
- Elena, this is MJ Akuda.

01:11.980 --> 01:13.313
MJ, this is Elena Roarke.

01:13.465 --> 01:15.223
- Thank you so much for coming.

01:15.301 --> 01:16.817
- Being here
where my mom passed,

01:16.893 --> 01:20.971
I'm hoping I will
feel her presence.

01:20.989 --> 01:22.823
- You will.

01:22.975 --> 01:25.400
Ash will take you to get
settled, and then we'll talk.

01:25.477 --> 01:28.903
I have a lot to tell you
about your mother, about Ruby.

01:28.923 --> 01:31.832
<i> [soft music]</i>

01:31.984 --> 01:33.258
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:33.335 --> 01:35.260
[chuckles]

01:35.337 --> 01:42.434
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:45.164 --> 01:46.939
- Good morning, Mrs. Beck.

01:47.015 --> 01:49.257
You ready for your massage?
- So ready.

01:49.335 --> 01:52.111
Let me just say bye
to my husband.

01:52.262 --> 01:53.520
See you later, babe.

01:53.597 --> 01:55.948
- Have a great time, baby.
Love you for life.

01:56.024 --> 01:59.284
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:59.511 --> 02:01.495
- Let's do this.

02:04.032 --> 02:05.791
- Oh, Brooklyn, come in.

02:05.868 --> 02:08.018
Sue and Jenna,
meet my associate, Ruby.

02:08.020 --> 02:09.853
- Hi, please.

02:09.855 --> 02:11.672
- Thank you.

02:13.208 --> 02:14.858
- Does Gavin suspect anything?

02:14.860 --> 02:17.377
- For all he knows, you two
are thousands of miles away,

02:17.529 --> 02:20.697
and I'm getting
a hot stone massage.

02:20.699 --> 02:24.476
- So let's talk
about what we're gonna do

02:24.628 --> 02:26.553
to this son of a bitch.

02:26.630 --> 02:29.481
<i> [dreamy music]</i>

02:29.633 --> 02:36.697
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:40.327 --> 02:42.310
<i> - Gavin and I met</i>
<i> when we were 20.</i>

02:42.388 --> 02:45.222
He was so damn handsome.

02:45.224 --> 02:46.481
- Still is.

02:46.575 --> 02:48.333
- You have to understand,
when Gavin looks at you,

02:48.485 --> 02:50.335
he makes you feel like
you're his whole world.

02:50.487 --> 02:52.337
I didn't even know
who I was yet,

02:52.414 --> 02:54.898
so I just became Gavin's wife.

02:54.991 --> 02:58.251
We had two children,
a house, dog.

02:58.328 --> 03:01.238
- What happened?
- She did.

03:01.240 --> 03:03.423
- He started
a health supplement company

03:03.517 --> 03:06.334
and suddenly started spending
more and more time at work,

03:06.353 --> 03:08.412
and I started smelling
the perfume.

03:08.472 --> 03:09.930
- My perfume.

03:10.006 --> 03:13.600
- I tried to talk to him,
but he gaslit me.

03:13.752 --> 03:15.936
He made me think I was crazy.

03:16.012 --> 03:18.680
I finally had myself committed.

03:18.699 --> 03:20.941
- That must have
been so painful.

03:21.093 --> 03:22.442
- It destroyed me.

03:22.594 --> 03:26.187
But I had already hired
a private investigator.

03:26.207 --> 03:28.281
And when I got
out of treatment,

03:28.434 --> 03:30.283
there were pictures
waiting for me.

03:30.436 --> 03:33.712
- Of Gavin and his head
of marketing.

03:33.863 --> 03:34.713
- You.

03:34.864 --> 03:36.122
- Unlike Sue,

03:36.199 --> 03:38.217
I knew exactly who I was,

03:38.293 --> 03:40.719
and Gavin played me
like a fiddle.

03:40.796 --> 03:44.205
He made me feel like I was the
smartest person in the room.

03:44.225 --> 03:47.893
He said my ambition
was an aphrodisiac.

03:48.044 --> 03:50.637
- Oh, that's good.

03:50.714 --> 03:53.139
- Then we got married,
and we threw ourselves

03:53.292 --> 03:54.791
into growing this company.

03:54.810 --> 03:56.293
- Of course
he started cheating.

03:56.386 --> 03:58.070
- And of course
he lied about it.

03:58.221 --> 03:59.980
I made that company.

04:00.132 --> 04:02.966
And then one day at lunch,

04:02.968 --> 04:05.911
he announced that he wanted
to move forward without me,

04:06.062 --> 04:09.155
both personally
and professionally.

04:09.308 --> 04:11.416
It's taken me years to recover.

04:11.568 --> 04:16.255
And if I'm being honest,
I'm still recovering.

04:16.331 --> 04:20.166
- And I'm the naive sap
who thought,

04:20.319 --> 04:22.002
third time's a charm.

04:22.154 --> 04:23.411
- Don't blame yourself.

04:23.430 --> 04:25.580
- You didn't stand a chance
against that charm,

04:25.657 --> 04:27.007
not at your age.

04:27.101 --> 04:31.011
- He told me he'd been focusing
on his company and his kids,

04:31.163 --> 04:33.163
that he forgot how to live.

04:33.165 --> 04:36.666
He said,
I brought him back to life.

04:36.668 --> 04:38.335
[both scoff]
- I know.

04:38.353 --> 04:40.003
My father saw
right through him,

04:40.005 --> 04:41.947
but I didn't listen.

04:42.098 --> 04:44.341
- But your father knew best.

04:44.359 --> 04:47.360
- Gavin's been cheating on me.

04:47.437 --> 04:49.121
When I got suspicious--

04:49.272 --> 04:51.515
- Then the gaslighting began.

04:51.517 --> 04:54.017
- Then one day, I ran
into Jen at the hair salon,

04:54.019 --> 04:55.460
and we started talking.

04:55.612 --> 04:58.446
- And we called Sue
and talked some more.

04:58.465 --> 05:02.968
- My dad died before I
could tell him he was right.

05:03.119 --> 05:05.211
- I'm so sorry.

05:05.364 --> 05:08.031
- The three of us
decided I should keep

05:08.033 --> 05:10.309
playing wifey, bide my time.

05:10.460 --> 05:13.553
- We knew we had to do
something to make it right.

05:13.630 --> 05:16.964
- So, ladies, what can
the Island do for you?

05:17.042 --> 05:20.635
- Our fantasy is to get
revenge on our husband.

05:20.712 --> 05:22.879
- We want him to feel
as awful as he's made us feel.

05:22.898 --> 05:24.489
- We want him to hurt.

05:24.641 --> 05:27.050
- You should know
that revenge fantasies

05:27.052 --> 05:28.401
don't always end well.

05:28.554 --> 05:31.054
- Mm, we'll take our chances.
- Very well.

05:31.073 --> 05:37.336
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:37.412 --> 05:40.914
What's in this box
is very powerful.

05:41.008 --> 05:43.342
Together,
you'll decide how to use it.

05:43.493 --> 05:46.494
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:46.513 --> 05:50.090
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have somewhere to be.

05:50.166 --> 05:52.017
Ruby will show you
to your suites.

05:52.094 --> 05:55.002
And welcome to Fantasy Island.

05:55.080 --> 05:59.766
- Right this way, Mrs. Becks.

05:59.918 --> 06:01.008
Okay.

06:01.028 --> 06:08.367
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:09.185 --> 06:13.187
- MJ, welcome to my home.

06:13.265 --> 06:15.281
- It's paradise.

06:15.434 --> 06:16.950
- You already met Javier,

06:17.102 --> 06:19.193
and this is Segundo,
the island's caretaker.

06:19.271 --> 06:20.379
- Hey.

06:20.530 --> 06:24.274
- Your eyes are just
as your mother described,

06:24.276 --> 06:26.868
chocolate derretido.

06:26.945 --> 06:28.970
- Right this way.

06:31.466 --> 06:34.709
- Why does this feel
like an intervention?

06:34.786 --> 06:39.231
- What I'm about to tell you
is going to be quite shocking.

06:39.382 --> 06:42.067
Javier and Segundo,
they know Ruby,

06:42.294 --> 06:43.402
so they can help me explain.

06:43.553 --> 06:46.129
- MJ, I flew your parents
to the island.

06:46.148 --> 06:49.649
A few days later,
I took your dad home alone.

06:49.726 --> 06:52.894
It was one of the toughest
flights of my life.

06:52.988 --> 06:55.730
- You mean, they knew her--

06:55.749 --> 06:57.565
past tense.

06:57.584 --> 07:00.419
- What did your father tell you
about your mother's death?

07:00.495 --> 07:03.997
- He said there was
a waterfall and dancing,

07:04.073 --> 07:06.316
and that she got a tattoo,
which is, like,

07:06.318 --> 07:09.577
so hard to imagine.

07:09.596 --> 07:12.264
Then the morning they were
supposed to leave, she died.

07:13.341 --> 07:16.250
- That is not
exactly what happened.

07:16.270 --> 07:18.687
Although, she did get a tattoo.

07:22.167 --> 07:24.359
- Shall we?

07:26.763 --> 07:28.613
Oh.

07:28.765 --> 07:30.282
- [gasps]
- [chuckles]

07:30.433 --> 07:34.010
- I don't get it.
- I think I do.

07:34.029 --> 07:35.695
And I like it.

07:35.772 --> 07:37.514
Let me see that.

07:37.516 --> 07:38.698
- Oh, my gosh.

07:38.792 --> 07:40.366
- A poppet
is a sympathetic doll,

07:40.519 --> 07:42.610
which means when
it's married to a person--

07:42.629 --> 07:45.355
- Interesting choice of words.

07:45.373 --> 07:49.116
- That person will feel
what the doll feels,

07:49.194 --> 07:51.861
whether that be pleasure
or pain,

07:51.880 --> 07:53.546
emphasis on pain.

07:53.623 --> 07:57.383
- Well, it's time for Gavin
to get married again.

07:57.460 --> 07:59.978
- Mm-hmm.
- Okay, so how do we do it?

08:00.129 --> 08:04.207
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

08:04.209 --> 08:06.876
- Hey, here she is.

08:06.878 --> 08:09.470
How was your massage?
- So, so good.

08:09.548 --> 08:10.822
[phone buzzing]

08:10.899 --> 08:12.215
- Oh.

08:12.234 --> 08:14.141
- Everything okay?

08:14.219 --> 08:15.977
- Yeah, yeah, it was just work.

08:15.996 --> 08:17.478
I told them not
to bother me on vacation.

08:17.498 --> 08:20.815
- Oh, so I get
you all to myself?

08:20.834 --> 08:22.334
- Yes, you do.

08:22.485 --> 08:24.394
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:24.396 --> 08:26.730
- Ow.
- Oh, sorry.

08:26.748 --> 08:28.990
There's a little spider, honey.

08:29.009 --> 08:30.992
I'm gonna run
to the little girl's room.

08:31.011 --> 08:33.419
- Hurry back, bunny rabbit.

08:33.496 --> 08:36.906
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:36.908 --> 08:39.851
- I got it.

08:40.003 --> 08:41.520
- Give me, give me.

08:41.596 --> 08:43.671
- Okay, it says
to put it in his pocket.

08:43.690 --> 08:44.914
- Okay.

08:44.933 --> 08:46.674
- Oh, and now what?

08:46.693 --> 08:50.845
- Now we are to join hands.

08:50.864 --> 08:52.422
Okay.

08:52.424 --> 08:56.092
Beginning, middle, and end,
to our aim you bend.

08:56.111 --> 09:01.665
His will is ours to rend,
his soul to apprehend.

09:03.935 --> 09:05.359
Come on.

09:05.379 --> 09:07.546
- How do we know if it worked?

09:11.034 --> 09:12.717
- Ow, my nuts!

09:12.794 --> 09:15.387
- It worked.
[laughter]

09:15.538 --> 09:19.540
- This is the best day
of my life.

09:19.618 --> 09:22.227
- So you're saying
my mom didn't die.

09:22.378 --> 09:25.138
She is alive and well
and 25 years old,

09:25.214 --> 09:27.140
and she lives on this island.

09:27.216 --> 09:29.901
But she doesn't remember me,
or my brothers, or my dad.

09:29.978 --> 09:32.145
Oh, and after 50 years
of marriage,

09:32.221 --> 09:33.963
she is now
in love with a woman.

09:33.965 --> 09:35.298
- Who is also a mermaid.

09:35.300 --> 09:38.301
- It's a lot, we know.

09:38.303 --> 09:40.303
- Your mother needs your help.

09:40.322 --> 09:42.322
If she doesn't get
her memories back,

09:42.474 --> 09:43.990
she may choose
to go away with Isla,

09:44.067 --> 09:46.067
and we're gonna lose her.

09:46.903 --> 09:51.072
- My mama, who is dead,
always told me,

09:51.091 --> 09:54.092
if I meet a crazy person,
I should get to stepping.

09:54.911 --> 09:56.836
Well, you all are crazy.

09:56.988 --> 09:58.096
And here I go.

09:58.247 --> 10:01.266
<i> [soft music]</i>

10:01.493 --> 10:07.439
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:07.590 --> 10:11.592
- Oh, my, who are you?

10:11.670 --> 10:13.945
- This is MJ Akuda.

10:14.022 --> 10:18.007
- Well, MJ Akuda,
you must be a special guest

10:18.026 --> 10:20.267
if Elena invited you
to her beach house.

10:20.345 --> 10:21.786
I never even knew
this place existed.

10:21.863 --> 10:24.438
- MJ recently lost her mother,
and she's come to the island

10:24.458 --> 10:25.439
to process her grief.

10:25.533 --> 10:27.183
I was thinking
the two of you could

10:27.185 --> 10:28.034
spend some time together.

10:28.111 --> 10:29.535
- Of course, yes.

10:29.688 --> 10:33.022
Oh, you came
to the right place to heal.

10:33.024 --> 10:36.051
Welcome to Fantasy Island.

10:40.215 --> 10:44.868
- A toast to mini Gavin,
taking one for the team.

10:44.870 --> 10:48.388
all: To mini Gavin!
[laughter]

10:48.464 --> 10:51.708
- Oh, I need another hit
of revenge endorphins.

10:51.726 --> 10:53.652
- It does suck, though.

10:53.728 --> 10:54.878
- What?

10:54.896 --> 10:56.488
- That we have
to keep on hiding.

10:56.564 --> 10:59.215
I want a front row seat
to his suffering.

10:59.234 --> 11:01.050
- You're terrifying.

11:01.052 --> 11:03.403
- That might not be
totally impossible.

11:03.479 --> 11:04.387
- Oh?

11:04.389 --> 11:06.239
- This book is full of tricks.

11:06.391 --> 11:10.669
I mean, look--
acid, binding, bleeding.

11:10.745 --> 11:12.061
- Promising.

11:12.080 --> 11:14.172
- Oh, here it is, yes, eyes.

11:14.399 --> 11:16.416
To prevent the enchanted person
from seeing

11:16.568 --> 11:20.586
particular objects or people,
rub the poppet's eyes

11:20.663 --> 11:24.999
with saliva
and say the following words.

11:25.076 --> 11:27.394
Hm, okay.

11:29.189 --> 11:32.607
Whoever you see, do not see me.

11:36.363 --> 11:41.257
- Whoever you see,
do not see me.

11:41.259 --> 11:42.942
That ought to do it.

11:43.094 --> 11:45.495
- Let the games begin.

11:47.782 --> 11:49.782
- My mom and dad
sat us all down

11:49.935 --> 11:52.919
and broke the news
that she was sick.

11:53.880 --> 11:56.047
It was the worst day
of my life.

11:56.124 --> 11:58.174
- I'm so sorry.

11:59.702 --> 12:01.945
- I thought my parents were
so in love all those years,

12:01.963 --> 12:06.725
but now I don't think
I really knew her.

12:07.802 --> 12:10.803
- Well, no doubt
she had her secrets.

12:10.880 --> 12:12.622
We all do.

12:12.624 --> 12:15.442
But I'm sure
you knew her heart.

12:19.130 --> 12:23.299
- What about you, Ruby?
How long have you lived here?

12:23.301 --> 12:28.913
- Oh, well,
feels like my whole life,

12:29.065 --> 12:32.542
like nothing ever existed
before here.

12:33.995 --> 12:35.962
- Ruby?

12:37.090 --> 12:39.406
Hola, Ruby.

12:39.459 --> 12:40.908
Who is this?

12:40.969 --> 12:44.411
- MJ, meet Isla.

12:44.431 --> 12:46.931
MJ lost her mom
not too long ago.

12:47.008 --> 12:51.844
- Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.

12:51.997 --> 12:56.165
Oh, I missed you.

12:56.167 --> 12:58.568
Can we talk?

12:59.854 --> 13:02.005
- Oh, yeah, sure.

13:02.007 --> 13:04.657
I'll just see you later.

13:06.678 --> 13:09.954
- Thanks for telling me
about your mama.

13:10.031 --> 13:16.628
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:16.630 --> 13:21.466
- Ruby, I want us
to start our life together.

13:21.617 --> 13:22.875
Why don't you?

13:23.028 --> 13:24.135
- I do.

13:24.287 --> 13:27.639
- Then say you'll come with me.

13:30.793 --> 13:32.385
- I will come with you.

13:32.537 --> 13:33.703
- Really?

13:33.721 --> 13:35.796
- Really.

13:35.816 --> 13:39.484
Will I have, like,
an actual tail?

13:39.711 --> 13:43.822
- Oh, you will be beautiful,
even more beautiful

13:43.898 --> 13:46.549
than you already are.

13:46.568 --> 13:50.811
- As soon as MJ's fantasy
is complete, we'll go.

13:50.831 --> 13:51.979
- Ruby.

13:52.057 --> 13:56.317
- It won't be long, I promise.

13:56.394 --> 14:03.174
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:03.401 --> 14:04.634
[laughter]

14:07.422 --> 14:09.422
- Good evening.
My name is Alyssa.

14:09.498 --> 14:11.741
Can I start you off
with some wine?

14:11.743 --> 14:13.242
- A chardonnay, please.

14:13.244 --> 14:17.263
- Alyssa, you look like you
have a sophisticated palate.

14:17.265 --> 14:18.581
- [scoffs]
- Surprise me.

14:18.583 --> 14:20.358
- Sophisticated palate.
- Unbelievable.

14:20.435 --> 14:23.086
- Well, there is
a smoky tequila I recommend.

14:23.088 --> 14:25.113
- Done.

14:26.925 --> 14:28.349
- Seriously?

14:28.368 --> 14:30.034
- What?
- You're with your wife.

14:30.186 --> 14:31.611
- [laughs]

14:31.763 --> 14:36.099
Honey, we really have to work
on this insecurity of yours.

14:36.101 --> 14:38.359
It's embarrassing.

14:38.453 --> 14:40.253
[groans]

14:41.197 --> 14:43.122
- What was that?
- What was what?

14:43.274 --> 14:45.458
- Did you just
kick me in the ass?

14:45.534 --> 14:47.293
- Honey, I'm all
the way over here.

14:47.445 --> 14:49.370
How could I kick
you in the ass?

14:49.389 --> 14:52.557
- Oh, must just be
that old glute injury

14:52.634 --> 14:54.058
of mine acting up.

14:54.210 --> 14:58.045
- Oh, yes, I have heard aches
and pains increase with age.

14:58.064 --> 14:59.972
- [laughs]

15:00.049 --> 15:02.025
- I have an idea.
- Okay.

15:04.979 --> 15:07.146
- You smell that?
- Smell what?

15:07.298 --> 15:10.299
- It's Carnal Flower
by Frédéric Malle.

15:10.318 --> 15:11.576
It's Jenna's perfume.

15:11.653 --> 15:13.152
- I don't smell anything.

15:13.304 --> 15:15.079
Maybe you're having a stroke.

15:15.231 --> 15:17.582
- My God,
is it possible she's here?

15:19.160 --> 15:21.920
- Sweetie,
she lives in New York.

15:21.996 --> 15:23.755
You're acting really paranoid.

15:23.831 --> 15:26.758
Oh, Alyssa,
we're ready to order.

15:26.834 --> 15:27.908
I'll have the fish.

15:27.928 --> 15:31.095
- [laughing]

15:34.417 --> 15:36.583
It's probably just jet lag.

15:36.661 --> 15:38.344
- Oh, I'll come back.

15:38.421 --> 15:39.270
- Great.

15:39.422 --> 15:40.680
- What's happening to me?

15:40.774 --> 15:43.849
- You are acting
so dramatic tonight.

15:44.002 --> 15:46.277
- Whoa, oh.

15:46.429 --> 15:49.489
[laughter]

15:51.434 --> 15:55.361
- Honey, that's--honey!
That's not appropriate.

15:55.513 --> 15:56.862
- I know that.

15:57.015 --> 15:59.515
Ah, oh!

15:59.534 --> 16:02.627
[groaning]

16:06.299 --> 16:08.282
Something's
really wrong with me.

16:08.359 --> 16:10.376
I got to get out of here.

16:10.528 --> 16:13.379
Sorry, guys.

16:13.531 --> 16:15.622
- Sorry.

16:16.201 --> 16:18.034
Honey, where are you going?

16:18.094 --> 16:19.202
You seem upset.

16:19.204 --> 16:20.219
- Of course I'm upset.

16:20.296 --> 16:22.872
I just humiliated myself
in there.

16:22.965 --> 16:25.374
- Honey, I'm worried about you.

16:25.393 --> 16:27.226
Should I call the doctor?

16:27.378 --> 16:28.544
Do you have the number
of that place

16:28.563 --> 16:31.047
that Sue went when she
was having her troubles?

16:31.065 --> 16:33.140
- [laughs]

16:33.218 --> 16:37.069
<i> [soft music]</i>

16:37.146 --> 16:40.906
- I'm gonna take a walk,
clear my head.

16:41.059 --> 16:43.743
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:43.895 --> 16:46.153
- Bye, sweetie.

16:46.231 --> 16:49.490
- Wow, you are pretty great
at this gaslighting thing.

16:49.567 --> 16:51.658
- Well, she learned
from a master.

16:51.678 --> 16:53.569
- Being mean is tiring.

16:53.571 --> 16:55.588
We should give him
a break for the night.

16:55.664 --> 16:59.350
- Well, excellent
first effort, witches.

16:59.427 --> 17:02.411
[laughter]

17:02.413 --> 17:09.085
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:09.103 --> 17:10.920
- [grunts]

17:10.922 --> 17:13.406
- [laughs]

17:18.946 --> 17:21.280
- I met your new guest.

17:21.357 --> 17:22.782
- MJ?

17:22.934 --> 17:24.358
Lovely young woman, yes.

17:24.377 --> 17:26.711
- She's Ruby's daughter,
isn't she?

17:28.364 --> 17:30.548
You're playing dirty.

17:33.461 --> 17:35.127
- I'm not playing.

17:35.204 --> 17:37.129
This is Ruby's life.

17:37.206 --> 17:39.282
- I will get what I want.

17:39.284 --> 17:43.803
- If you do,
I will never forgive myself.

17:43.955 --> 17:50.985
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:54.799 --> 17:56.632
- Double whiskey, neat.

17:56.634 --> 18:00.244
Actually, make it a triple,
one for each wife.

18:00.471 --> 18:01.487
- [chuckles]

18:01.564 --> 18:04.974
Sounds like there is
a story there, hm?

18:04.976 --> 18:08.252
- Two former, one current,
but I think

18:08.404 --> 18:13.015
they're all here,
messing with my mind.

18:13.075 --> 18:16.335
- I find a heartfelt apology

18:16.412 --> 18:20.080
is always
a good place to start.

18:20.100 --> 18:21.824
- Apologize?

18:21.843 --> 18:26.512
No, I'm gonna mess
with them right back.

18:26.664 --> 18:32.568
- Sometimes things are bad,
and sometimes things are worse.

18:33.504 --> 18:36.355
Better to stick with bad, hm?

18:36.507 --> 18:38.007
- [laughs]

18:38.009 --> 18:41.119
Thanks, old man,
but I got this.

18:53.040 --> 18:54.615
Hey, babe.

18:54.634 --> 18:56.634
- Are you okay, babe?

18:56.711 --> 18:58.970
You seemed so confused earlier.

18:59.046 --> 19:01.455
- You're right, I was.

19:01.474 --> 19:05.885
But now everything
is crystal clear.

19:06.037 --> 19:12.066
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:15.062 --> 19:18.305
<i> [soft music]</i>

19:18.383 --> 19:25.413
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:26.649 --> 19:30.651
- My mom loved the ocean.

19:30.728 --> 19:34.547
- Enough to dive in
and live there forever?

19:36.567 --> 19:40.178
Happens to be what I'm sitting
here trying to figure out,

19:40.254 --> 19:45.183
which probably sounds strange.

19:45.334 --> 19:48.761
- I have heard
stranger things recently.

19:48.837 --> 19:54.358
And, no, my mom knew how
dangerous the ocean could be.

19:54.510 --> 19:57.361
My brother almost drowned
when he was eight.

19:57.438 --> 20:00.114
- That must have
been terrifying.

20:01.776 --> 20:04.851
- Darren is his name,
my brother.

20:04.929 --> 20:09.432
- Huh, what a nice name.

20:09.434 --> 20:12.101
- My other brother's
name is Mac.

20:12.119 --> 20:15.104
It's Mac, Darren, and MJ.

20:15.122 --> 20:17.089
- Hm.
[chuckles]

20:19.444 --> 20:22.386
Anyway, we were at the beach--

20:22.538 --> 20:27.892
my dad Mel,
my mom, and us kids--

20:28.043 --> 20:30.953
and then a wave
knocked Darren over.

20:30.972 --> 20:32.304
He was so scrawny,

20:32.398 --> 20:35.882
the ocean
just sucked him right out.

20:35.960 --> 20:37.309
My mom dove in,

20:37.462 --> 20:39.812
almost drowned
getting him back.

20:39.964 --> 20:41.697
- She must have
been very brave.

20:43.892 --> 20:46.151
- I took her for granted.

20:46.228 --> 20:48.320
There's so many things I wish
I could have said to her,

20:48.397 --> 20:49.622
you know?

20:52.977 --> 20:54.810
- Tell her now.

20:54.829 --> 21:00.407
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:00.426 --> 21:02.426
- Mom,

21:02.503 --> 21:07.098
wow,
I really put you through it.

21:07.249 --> 21:09.116
I thought you didn't
understand me,

21:09.193 --> 21:14.105
but now I'm realizing you did,

21:14.256 --> 21:17.316
even when I didn't
understand myself.

21:20.671 --> 21:23.096
I'm happy, Mom.

21:23.116 --> 21:29.028
I got a job at a design firm,
and there's a guy.

21:29.180 --> 21:31.789
You'd love him.

21:31.866 --> 21:35.501
He's good, like dad.

21:37.688 --> 21:39.705
- You're doing great.

21:39.799 --> 21:41.757
Don't stop.

21:42.802 --> 21:45.720
- Also, Mom...

21:47.365 --> 21:50.382
I'm mad.

21:50.535 --> 21:53.536
I'm mad at you for not
letting me say goodbye,

21:53.629 --> 21:55.646
and I really miss you.

21:57.708 --> 22:01.736
- There now, she heard you.

22:03.564 --> 22:05.397
- I don't think so.

22:05.550 --> 22:06.882
Excuse me.

22:06.901 --> 22:13.998
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:18.062 --> 22:19.837
- Good book?

22:19.914 --> 22:22.173
- Mm-hmm.

22:22.324 --> 22:24.342
- It's been a weird vacation.

22:24.493 --> 22:26.251
- Has it?

22:26.404 --> 22:30.014
- But you're just
taking it all in stride.

22:30.016 --> 22:33.909
Reminds me of how
incredible you are for me.

22:33.928 --> 22:36.912
- You just used me
twice in a sentence.

22:36.931 --> 22:39.357
- See, and that's
what I love about you.

22:39.433 --> 22:42.676
You don't let me get away
with my usual BS.

22:42.753 --> 22:46.197
No one's ever gotten me
the way you do.

22:46.348 --> 22:47.923
Look, we both know
that I've struggled

22:47.942 --> 22:52.094
with fidelity in the past,
but I believe the right woman

22:52.113 --> 22:54.187
can change a man.

22:54.248 --> 22:57.083
- Okay.
- No, I mean it.

22:59.212 --> 23:03.381
Brooklyn Savannah Beck,
you are my forever.

23:03.532 --> 23:07.610
You make me a better man,
and that's why

23:07.703 --> 23:11.204
I want us to have a baby.

23:11.224 --> 23:12.464
- Are you serious?

23:12.558 --> 23:14.466
- As a heart attack.

23:14.560 --> 23:16.635
No more birth control.

23:16.787 --> 23:19.788
- Those are my Lexapro,
but I get the metaphor.

23:19.790 --> 23:21.565
- You want to start
trying right away?

23:21.642 --> 23:23.792
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

23:23.811 --> 23:27.571
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

23:27.648 --> 23:31.800
- Guys, guys, it worked.

23:31.819 --> 23:33.819
Our fantasy was a success.

23:33.913 --> 23:35.562
Gavin's grown.

23:35.581 --> 23:37.489
You should have heard
the things he said.

23:37.642 --> 23:39.083
- Let me guess.

23:39.160 --> 23:40.659
"The right woman
changes a man."

23:40.736 --> 23:43.445
- Or was it, "No one's ever
gotten me the way you do."

23:43.447 --> 23:47.091
- Okay, yes, but he means it.

23:47.126 --> 23:50.428
He told me he wants
to have a baby.

23:52.823 --> 23:56.100
What?
No, no, no, this is real.

23:56.251 --> 23:58.494
I've always wanted kids,
but, I mean,

23:58.512 --> 24:00.179
we could never find
the right time and--

24:00.273 --> 24:05.501
- Brooklyn, sweetie, there's
something you should know.

24:05.503 --> 24:07.503
- Sit down, honey.

24:07.505 --> 24:09.363
- What?

24:11.025 --> 24:15.119
- When we were married,
Gavin got a vasectomy.

24:15.270 --> 24:18.122
He can't have any more kids.

24:18.199 --> 24:20.708
- I'm so sorry, sweetheart.

24:22.036 --> 24:26.780
- That son of a bitch!

24:26.799 --> 24:29.282
- Brooklyn!

24:29.302 --> 24:31.877
- Uh-oh.
- This is gonna be fun.

24:32.029 --> 24:34.029
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

24:34.048 --> 24:36.456
- Brooklyn!

24:36.476 --> 24:38.124
- [gasping]

24:38.144 --> 24:40.219
- Brooklyn, open the door.

24:40.371 --> 24:41.553
Help me.

24:41.630 --> 24:42.963
- We've all wanted
to kill Gavin

24:43.040 --> 24:44.206
at some point in our life.

24:44.225 --> 24:45.874
- Open the door, Brooklyn.

24:45.876 --> 24:48.819
- Gavin destroyed my
relationship with my father.

24:48.971 --> 24:51.322
He lied to me.

24:51.473 --> 24:54.808
He's made a fool of me
for the last time.

24:54.827 --> 24:59.663
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:59.890 --> 25:01.557
- Enough.

25:01.575 --> 25:07.296
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:11.752 --> 25:13.752
- Hi.
- Morning.

25:13.829 --> 25:17.431
- I need you to tell Elena
that she brought the wrong kid.

25:18.959 --> 25:20.166
- I doubt that.

25:20.261 --> 25:22.853
- I'm telling you,
Darren could do this.

25:23.005 --> 25:24.429
Mac could do this.

25:24.582 --> 25:26.857
Seriously, if you could ask
my mom, she'd tell you that.

25:27.009 --> 25:29.193
- I know what your mom
thinks of you.

25:29.270 --> 25:30.528
I have a daughter
a little younger than you.

25:30.604 --> 25:31.845
We talk.

25:31.939 --> 25:34.698
- Then you know if you'd
asked her if I was the kid

25:34.850 --> 25:36.867
to convince the 50 years
younger version of her

25:37.019 --> 25:38.702
not to become a mermaid,
she would say--

25:38.929 --> 25:40.279
- Absolutely.

25:40.431 --> 25:42.264
Know what your mom calls you?

25:42.283 --> 25:43.707
- A pain in the ass.

25:43.784 --> 25:46.544
- A stubborn pain in the ass.

25:46.695 --> 25:49.213
She says it with pride.

25:49.364 --> 25:51.549
My daughter, Helene,
she's stubborn too.

25:51.625 --> 25:53.609
And she's had to be.

25:53.611 --> 25:56.295
Your mom needs you to be
a stubborn pain in the ass

25:56.371 --> 25:57.370
right now.

25:57.390 --> 25:59.932
She needs you to fight for her.

26:00.726 --> 26:02.785
- But why isn't she fighting?

26:02.803 --> 26:03.894
- She is.

26:03.971 --> 26:07.623
This magic she's up against
is powerful.

26:07.641 --> 26:11.476
- I just--how am I supposed
to compete with that?

26:11.629 --> 26:13.386
- The love you have
for your mom,

26:13.464 --> 26:15.147
that's its own kind of magic.

26:15.223 --> 26:18.317
<i> [soft music]</i>

26:18.393 --> 26:24.807
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:24.825 --> 26:28.310
- Ladies, your poppet
privileges have been revoked.

26:28.329 --> 26:30.145
- Well, it was fun
while it lasted.

26:30.164 --> 26:32.256
- Screw that stupid doll.

26:32.333 --> 26:35.075
Gavin still doesn't get it.
He'll never get it.

26:35.094 --> 26:36.485
- This whole thing
is pointless.

26:36.578 --> 26:38.837
- Oh, all right then.

26:38.989 --> 26:40.914
I guess we're done.

26:40.933 --> 26:42.582
- Wait.

26:42.602 --> 26:45.102
We asked for the wrong thing,
didn't we?

26:45.253 --> 26:46.845
We asked to make him hurt,

26:46.997 --> 26:48.664
but that's not
really what we want.

26:48.666 --> 26:50.608
- What do you want, really?

26:50.759 --> 26:52.351
- I want to make him hurt.

26:52.427 --> 26:55.446
- I want to be free of him.

26:55.522 --> 27:00.433
I am tired
of Gavin Beck defining me.

27:00.453 --> 27:03.846
- He's never gonna understand.

27:03.864 --> 27:05.180
He's defective.

27:05.349 --> 27:09.275
- On this island, people's
capabilities often evolve.

27:09.295 --> 27:11.277
I believe we can
channel your tears

27:11.355 --> 27:13.756
to a more productive end.

27:14.692 --> 27:18.861
- Brooklyn, are you here?

27:18.863 --> 27:19.878
Brooklyn.

27:20.030 --> 27:21.805
- Duerme.

27:21.957 --> 27:24.808
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

27:24.960 --> 27:32.024
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:35.821 --> 27:37.229
- What the hell is this?

27:37.305 --> 27:39.156
- The Throne of Tears.

27:39.233 --> 27:41.049
- Look, I don't
know who you are,

27:41.068 --> 27:42.159
but get me out of this thing.

27:42.236 --> 27:44.644
- You know, Dr. Beck,
I try very hard

27:44.664 --> 27:46.722
not to be judgmental.

27:46.724 --> 27:48.648
But people like you
who cause others pain

27:48.668 --> 27:52.728
with zero consideration,
who manipulate and lie

27:52.730 --> 27:56.248
to those they say they love,
you make it very difficult.

27:56.400 --> 27:58.250
- Wah-wah, give me a break.

27:58.326 --> 27:59.418
- You'll find a break

27:59.494 --> 28:00.844
is the last thing
you're gonna get here.

28:00.996 --> 28:01.920
- I'm gonna sue your ass.

28:01.997 --> 28:03.906
- [chuckles]

28:03.924 --> 28:05.165
You're up, ladies.

28:05.242 --> 28:06.408
- What do we need to do?

28:06.427 --> 28:09.186
- Just tell him what
he needs to hear.

28:09.337 --> 28:16.360
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:20.032 --> 28:22.849
- Hi, I'm on my way to meet MJ.

28:22.868 --> 28:24.851
- It's time, Ruby.
- Time?

28:24.929 --> 28:26.445
No, I'm not ready.

28:26.597 --> 28:28.947
- I'm afraid if we wait,
you'll change your mind.

28:29.099 --> 28:31.083
- Hey, I told you.

28:32.194 --> 28:34.453
- Come with me now.

28:34.547 --> 28:36.438
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:36.457 --> 28:38.957
Be one of us.

28:39.034 --> 28:41.534
Choose to be with me.

28:41.554 --> 28:43.128
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:43.205 --> 28:46.056
You have to say it, Ruby.

28:46.133 --> 28:48.450
Say you choose.

28:48.452 --> 28:52.396
Say,
"I choose to be one of you."

28:52.473 --> 28:54.380
- I choose--

28:54.458 --> 28:56.716
- Mama, no!

28:56.794 --> 29:00.887
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:00.906 --> 29:02.481
Mama!

29:02.633 --> 29:04.316
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:04.392 --> 29:05.634
- Let go!

29:05.652 --> 29:07.745
- No!
- Ahh!

29:07.896 --> 29:10.989
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:11.141 --> 29:12.732
- Mama.

29:12.810 --> 29:14.567
- MJ!

29:14.587 --> 29:16.920
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:16.997 --> 29:19.923
- [shrieks]

29:20.000 --> 29:27.097
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:28.434 --> 29:31.560
- [coughing]

29:34.089 --> 29:40.018
- Mama, Mama,
please don't leave me again.

29:40.170 --> 29:44.339
- MJ, my sweet girl.

29:44.358 --> 29:49.344
You saved me.
You saved me.

29:49.346 --> 29:54.082
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:57.354 --> 29:58.278
- Where did Dad go to college?

29:58.297 --> 30:00.372
- Morehouse, class of '69.

30:00.524 --> 30:03.634
- [chuckles]
What's Darren's middle name?

30:03.710 --> 30:05.785
- Wilbur.

30:05.805 --> 30:08.363
I don't know what
we were thinking.

30:08.365 --> 30:11.433
[laughter]

30:13.813 --> 30:17.556
- How many car accidents
did I get into in high school?

30:17.632 --> 30:19.207
- Well, there's the two
that I know about

30:19.226 --> 30:22.544
and then the one that you think
I don't know about.

30:22.546 --> 30:24.988
- I could never hide
anything from you.

30:25.140 --> 30:28.408
- But you sure tried.

30:29.829 --> 30:32.496
Oh, my girl,

30:32.573 --> 30:36.333
you got through to me
when no one else could.

30:36.410 --> 30:40.896
- Javier said, "Love
is its own kind of magic."

30:40.898 --> 30:43.248
Guess he was right.

30:43.400 --> 30:46.568
- This must be all
so strange for you,

30:46.587 --> 30:51.164
a magical island,
seeing me like this.

30:51.241 --> 30:53.166
- I'm kind of used to it.

30:53.185 --> 30:56.336
It's actually pretty cool.

30:56.355 --> 30:58.747
- You just have
the most incredible ability

30:58.749 --> 31:00.749
to take people as they are.

31:00.751 --> 31:04.177
- I think we both know
that's not always good.

31:04.196 --> 31:07.923
- Well, sometimes
people disappoint.

31:07.925 --> 31:09.774
- Like me.

31:09.869 --> 31:11.684
<i> [soft music]</i>

31:11.762 --> 31:15.263
I know I disappointed you,
Mom, and I am so sorry.

31:15.265 --> 31:20.952
- No, I will not let you say
you're sorry

31:21.029 --> 31:23.380
for being you.

31:23.531 --> 31:28.868
Yes, you learned some things
the hard way,

31:28.888 --> 31:31.113
but you learned.

31:31.131 --> 31:34.132
And now look at you.

31:34.284 --> 31:37.786
You are my pride and joy.

31:37.788 --> 31:40.956
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:40.958 --> 31:43.883
Don't tell Darren and Mac
I said that.

31:43.961 --> 31:45.051
- [laughs]

31:45.129 --> 31:47.362
Promise.

31:50.134 --> 31:52.743
I really miss you, Mama.

31:54.471 --> 32:01.543
- Baby, I miss you
every moment of every day.

32:04.148 --> 32:06.982
And I wish I could be with you.

32:07.000 --> 32:10.835
- I understand that you can't.

32:10.988 --> 32:16.174
And I am so happy that you
get to live your life again

32:16.326 --> 32:20.345
and be exactly who you are.

32:20.422 --> 32:25.333
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:25.352 --> 32:28.353
- How did I bring such
a spectacular light

32:28.505 --> 32:30.005
in this world?

32:30.007 --> 32:31.889
- You just got lucky.

32:31.967 --> 32:33.784
[laughter]

32:33.860 --> 32:35.902
- Come here.

32:36.013 --> 32:39.122
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:39.349 --> 32:42.793
- You love this,
don't you, seeing me suffer?

32:42.869 --> 32:46.129
- I gave you
the best years of my life.

32:46.281 --> 32:49.282
I gave you children, a home.

32:49.301 --> 32:51.710
You still don't get it,
but you will.

32:51.862 --> 32:53.453
- I made you,

32:53.472 --> 32:56.047
and you threw me out
like a piece of trash.

32:56.200 --> 32:58.141
- Check your bank account,
Jenna.

32:58.218 --> 33:00.218
You were well compensated
for your trouble.

33:00.295 --> 33:02.204
- What's wrong with you?

33:02.206 --> 33:04.314
- I chose you
over my own father.

33:04.466 --> 33:06.558
I should have been
with him when he died.

33:06.634 --> 33:08.819
I don't know what
I ever even saw in you.

33:08.895 --> 33:11.804
- You stole my ability
to trust anyone,

33:11.824 --> 33:13.156
including myself.

33:13.308 --> 33:15.383
- You took advantage
of my love.

33:15.402 --> 33:17.886
- I was so blinded
by your lies,

33:17.888 --> 33:20.646
I thought the bouquet of red
flags you gave me were roses.

33:20.724 --> 33:22.165
- Why are you doing this?

33:22.317 --> 33:23.983
- Because
you need to understand,

33:24.003 --> 33:25.744
so we can move on.

33:25.896 --> 33:27.487
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:27.564 --> 33:30.582
- [groaning]

33:30.734 --> 33:32.342
Oh, it hurts so much.

33:32.494 --> 33:35.161
- It's the Throne of Tears,
Gavin.

33:35.239 --> 33:36.829
That's what you're
being drenched in,

33:36.849 --> 33:40.909
our tears and the tears of all
the women who cried over you.

33:40.927 --> 33:43.745
- With every drop,
you feel the pain

33:43.764 --> 33:45.522
we felt when we cried them.

33:45.599 --> 33:50.418
- Oh, oh, it feels like
there's acid in my chest.

33:50.420 --> 33:53.196
Oh, I can't breathe, the pain.

33:53.423 --> 33:55.423
- This is what it's like,
Gavin.

33:55.425 --> 33:57.868
This is what
it's like to love you.

33:58.019 --> 33:59.427
- I did this to you?

33:59.429 --> 34:02.855
- You did this to all of us.

34:02.933 --> 34:04.041
- I'm sorry.

34:04.192 --> 34:06.192
I'm so sorry.

34:06.211 --> 34:09.621
Please forgive me.

34:09.623 --> 34:14.626
Please, please forgive me.

34:14.702 --> 34:16.536
Please, forgive me.

34:16.555 --> 34:23.643
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:46.901 --> 34:49.811
- Don't come near me.

34:49.830 --> 34:51.088
- Ruby.

34:51.164 --> 34:54.091
- I do not choose
to go with you,

34:54.242 --> 34:55.741
and I never will.

34:55.761 --> 34:57.076
- I do love you.

34:57.096 --> 35:00.155
- You don't even know me.

35:00.157 --> 35:04.342
Mel, my children,

35:04.494 --> 35:09.922
my family and friends,
they are who I am,

35:09.942 --> 35:11.257
and you erased them.

35:11.335 --> 35:16.004
- You would have been happy
with us, with me.

35:16.022 --> 35:18.356
- Not real happiness.

35:18.450 --> 35:21.267
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:21.345 --> 35:23.511
- If you change your mind,

35:23.530 --> 35:27.015
all you have to do
is think of me.

35:27.017 --> 35:28.700
- I won't.

35:28.776 --> 35:34.022
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:34.024 --> 35:37.859
- When you threw this
into the ocean,

35:37.878 --> 35:41.212
I was there.

35:41.365 --> 35:45.124
I thought one day
you might want it back.

35:45.144 --> 35:47.719
- My wedding ring.

35:47.795 --> 35:54.693
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

35:57.214 --> 35:59.990
- Goodbye, Ruby.

36:34.175 --> 36:37.843
<i> [soft music]</i>

36:37.921 --> 36:40.088
- Safe trip.

36:40.106 --> 36:43.925
- Good morning, Becks.
I hope you enjoyed your stay.

36:43.944 --> 36:45.702
- We absolutely did.

36:45.779 --> 36:48.020
- Some of us more than others.

36:48.098 --> 36:50.207
- I hated it,

36:50.283 --> 36:53.651
but I got
what I needed and deserved.

36:53.729 --> 36:56.713
- And what you deserve
is what we all needed.

36:56.940 --> 36:58.773
- My father
would be proud of me

36:58.775 --> 37:02.219
for standing up for myself
and letting go.

37:02.370 --> 37:04.279
- Whatever comes next,

37:04.281 --> 37:06.723
it won't have anything
to do with Gavin.

37:06.800 --> 37:10.876
No offense, or offense,
whichever.

37:10.954 --> 37:12.395
- What about you, Gavin?

37:12.547 --> 37:14.880
- I just know
that I don't ever want

37:14.958 --> 37:17.308
to make anyone else feel
the way that I've made

37:17.461 --> 37:19.127
Sue, Jenna, and Brooklyn feel.

37:19.145 --> 37:20.311
- Well, if you
ever want to come back

37:20.405 --> 37:23.631
to the island for a refresher,
just let me know.

37:23.633 --> 37:29.246
- That sounds so generous,
but it feels like a threat.

37:29.397 --> 37:32.398
- Safe travels.
- Thank you.

37:32.417 --> 37:34.501
- Thank you.

37:36.663 --> 37:37.737
- Hi.

37:37.831 --> 37:40.406
- Thank you
for not giving up on my mom.

37:40.484 --> 37:42.742
- Never.

37:42.836 --> 37:44.761
- Thank you.

37:44.912 --> 37:47.913
<i> [Annie Drury's</i>
<i> "You Took Me Dancing"]</i>

37:47.933 --> 37:50.100
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:50.251 --> 37:54.662
I love you, Mary Jane Akuda.

37:54.664 --> 37:57.515
Don't you ever forget that.

37:57.667 --> 37:59.517
- I love you, Mama.

37:59.669 --> 38:01.169
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:01.262 --> 38:03.780
<i> - ♪ Lights go out ♪</i>

38:03.857 --> 38:04.781
<i> [mystical whoosh]</i>

38:04.932 --> 38:07.509
<i> ♪ I've got my best dress on ♪</i>

38:07.511 --> 38:10.436
<i> ♪ You keep a fire light ♪</i>

38:10.455 --> 38:13.439
- I think I've come to terms
with my mom's death.

38:13.458 --> 38:15.350
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:15.368 --> 38:20.872
I'm not sure how,
but a burden has been lifted.

38:21.024 --> 38:23.466
- I'm glad we could help.

38:23.618 --> 38:29.213
- Um, your mother wrote these
while she was here,

38:29.290 --> 38:32.642
one for each of her babies.

38:32.719 --> 38:38.373
- Oh, I'll make sure
my brothers get them.

38:38.391 --> 38:43.820
- Also, she wanted you
to have this.

38:43.971 --> 38:46.548
- Her wedding ring.

38:46.550 --> 38:51.143
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:51.221 --> 38:54.331
I'll treasure it.

38:54.407 --> 38:58.651
Thank you both
for everything.

38:58.670 --> 39:00.986
Thank you.

39:01.064 --> 39:03.064
- Yeah.

39:03.066 --> 39:08.236
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:08.254 --> 39:11.097
- Did I tell you
my mom's name was Ruby?

39:13.410 --> 39:16.260
You remind me of her.

39:16.337 --> 39:20.857
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:21.050 --> 39:23.342
<i> - ♪ There's something</i>
<i> I know ♪</i>

39:23.420 --> 39:24.602
- Ruby.

39:24.679 --> 39:27.589
<i> - ♪ Goodness leaks</i>
<i> through your bones ♪</i>

39:27.591 --> 39:31.034
<i> ♪ There's just something</i>
<i> about the way ♪</i>

39:31.185 --> 39:36.114
<i> ♪ You make me feel at home ♪</i>

39:36.266 --> 39:40.359
<i> ♪ And I love what you do ♪</i>

39:40.437 --> 39:45.440
- It's your welcome back party,
so welcome back.

39:45.442 --> 39:48.109
- Oh, it is good to be back.

39:48.128 --> 39:49.219
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

39:49.295 --> 39:50.461
- Salud.

39:50.555 --> 39:52.947
- Personally,
I prefer you without fins.

39:52.966 --> 39:54.057
[laughter]

39:54.208 --> 39:56.375
- Thank you, Segundo.

39:56.395 --> 39:58.377
- Miss Roarke,
where do you want the music?

39:58.471 --> 40:00.471
- Oh.

40:00.624 --> 40:03.566
- MJ told me what
you said about love

40:03.643 --> 40:05.810
being its own kind of magic.

40:05.962 --> 40:08.738
Very wise.

40:08.890 --> 40:11.223
So stop being dumb.

40:11.243 --> 40:13.801
Even when you get
to do it twice,

40:13.820 --> 40:16.804
life is too short
to waste time.

40:16.823 --> 40:23.420
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:23.571 --> 40:24.996
- Excuse me.

40:25.148 --> 40:29.000
<i> - ♪ You still</i>
<i> take me dancing ♪</i>

40:29.002 --> 40:33.412
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:33.432 --> 40:34.672
- Elena--

40:34.824 --> 40:36.248
- I'm sorry.
You were right.

40:36.268 --> 40:37.825
Everything you said was right.

40:37.844 --> 40:39.677
I made a decision
that we should have

40:39.829 --> 40:40.437
made together, Javier, so--

40:40.513 --> 40:41.829
- Elena--

40:41.940 --> 40:43.998
- And I am so sorry that I
made you feel like a guest.

40:44.000 --> 40:45.942
You know, I love my guests.

40:46.093 --> 40:47.944
They're very important to me,
but not like you.

40:48.171 --> 40:49.261
- Can I go now?

40:49.339 --> 40:51.355
- Yes, yeah, go now.

40:51.508 --> 40:52.340
- Okay.

40:52.342 --> 40:53.950
Elena, if we're gonna do this,

40:54.101 --> 40:56.360
I need to know that
when hard things come up,

40:56.437 --> 40:59.681
which they will,
we'll handle them together.

40:59.683 --> 41:02.292
- Yeah, together, 100%.

41:02.294 --> 41:03.868
- Good.

41:04.020 --> 41:05.128
Now, I kind of want
to hear what

41:05.279 --> 41:07.112
you said the other night
straight from you,

41:07.190 --> 41:08.856
not just in my head.

41:08.875 --> 41:11.042
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:11.194 --> 41:13.118
- I want to rip your shirt off?

41:13.196 --> 41:16.789
- After that.

41:16.866 --> 41:18.549
- I love you.

41:18.702 --> 41:22.795
- Good, because I love you,
Elena Roarke.

41:22.797 --> 41:25.039
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:25.132 --> 41:28.818
[cell phone rings]

41:28.970 --> 41:31.362
- You should get that.

41:32.899 --> 41:34.549
- It's Helene.

41:34.567 --> 41:37.051
Helene.
Hey, kiddo.

41:37.053 --> 41:38.402
- Dadvier!

41:38.479 --> 41:40.054
<i> Oh, Elena.</i>

41:40.073 --> 41:42.406
<i> Oh, I love the energy there.</i>

41:42.483 --> 41:43.816
- God, I miss you.

41:43.835 --> 41:46.318
I wish you were here.
We're having a party for Ruby.

41:46.338 --> 41:48.988
<i> - Mm, I heard about that.</i>

41:49.065 --> 41:51.082
<i> [laughs]</i>

41:51.158 --> 41:53.417
all: Surprise!

41:53.494 --> 41:54.902
- You did this.

41:54.904 --> 41:58.056
- Go, silly, go.

41:59.851 --> 42:03.911
- Welcome to the island.
- Helene, Helene.

42:03.930 --> 42:07.172
- Okay, I got to breathe.

42:07.250 --> 42:09.508
- Welcome home.

42:09.586 --> 42:11.444
[glass ringing]
- Thank you.

42:14.774 --> 42:20.428
- Until recently, I thought I
had friends on Fantasy Island,

42:20.430 --> 42:22.446
but I don't.

42:22.599 --> 42:25.190
I have family.

42:25.210 --> 42:28.694
Family are the people
who fight for you,

42:28.713 --> 42:31.214
even when you make mistakes,

42:31.365 --> 42:36.277
who remind you of
who you are when you forget,

42:36.296 --> 42:41.299
who save you
when you need saving,

42:41.393 --> 42:43.284
or even better,

42:43.286 --> 42:47.605
give you what you need
to save yourself.

42:49.809 --> 42:51.309
[sighs]

42:51.461 --> 42:53.052
To family.

42:53.129 --> 42:54.478
- To family.

42:54.555 --> 42:56.698
all: To family.

42:58.076 --> 42:59.984
<i> - Whoo, yes!</i>

43:00.061 --> 43:01.986
- Eso, whoo!

43:02.063 --> 43:04.488
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

43:04.641 --> 43:07.141
Venga, venga!

43:07.143 --> 43:09.827
<i> - ♪ I feel like dancing ♪</i>

43:09.904 --> 43:11.312
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:11.331 --> 43:13.815
<i> ♪ I feel like dancing ♪</i>

43:13.833 --> 43:15.650
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:15.652 --> 43:16.718
<i> ♪ I feel like-- ♪</i>

43:19.656 --> 43:19.971
<i> [dreamy music]</i>

43:23.660 --> 43:30.565
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
